result.execSummary:
The defendant Matthew A Youngbauer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(>50g) [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)4.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Maintain full time employment.  At least 30 hours per week.
AODA Assessment and follow through on all recommendations of Counselor.
As a convicted felon, prohibited from possessing a firearm.
Cognitive Behavior Class as directed by DOC agent.
As a convicted felon, prohibited from voting until civil rights restored.

Maintain absolute sobriety.  Random UA's as requested by agent.    Defendant is to submit DNA sample.

Amended 7-26-2016:  The charges of Possess with Intent - Amphetamine (>3-10g), Possession of THC and Possession of Drug Paraphernalia in Burnett Co. Case No. 15CF140 be read in and dismissed as part of the disposition.

Defendant Matthew A Youngbauer is in custody and appears in court with attorney Joel Kenneth Larimore.   Fred Bourg, Amber Hahn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
State calls Jerry Katchka sworn and questioned by Ms. Hahn.  Exhibits #1 - #13 marked.  Witness identifies Lance Gordon and Daniel Harvey from exhibits #1 and #2.  Witness identifies John Macoon Peterson from exhibit #3.  Witness identifies Rebecca Tochaulaski from exhibit #4.  Witness identifies Darryl Nelis from exhibit #5.  Witness explains interview information regarding delivery of meth into Bayfield County, Ashland County and Red Cliff.  Witness identifies Christie Nelson from exhibit #6.  Witness identifies Garrit Pederson from exhibit #7.  Witness identifies James Warren from exhibit #8.  Witness identifies Dakota Gordon from exhibit #9.  Witness identifies Jeremy Stroebel from exhibit #10.  Witness identifies Tabitha Zwetow from exhibit #11.  Witness identifies Daniel Thoreson Sr. from exhibit #12.  Witness indicates he helped execute Search Warrants for Garrit Pederson's residence and Daniel Thoreson Sr. residence.  Witness identifies Defendant in person and from exhibit #13.  Used field tests for substances found and testing was positive as meth.  Those interviewed indicated Mr. Youngbauer was the main individual selling in Bayfield County.  State offers exhibits #1 through #13; Court receives with no objection by defense.  Cross by Atty Larimore.  Lots of information was brought in from many sources.  No Re-Direct.  No further witnesses of the State.  No witnesses of the Defense.  Argument by Ms. Hahn; asks for bind over.  Argument by Atty Larimore.  Ct:  finds probable cause; bound over for arraignment.  
Atty Hahn asks to appear by telephone for the arraignment.  Arraignment scheduled for 01-26-2016 at 9:45 a.m.  Bond continues.
